title: Killer Queens of England   (2002 - Complete Series)
description:
TV : Documentary : TV quality : English


Killer Queens (2002)

This series charts the lives of five notorious women who gained fame or repute for their willingness to fight, scheme, and even die for their principles.

From Boudicca's vengeful rebellion against the Romans in 43 A.D. to Lady Mary Banks' courageous defense of Corfe Castle in 1643, explore the history and motivations of these determined Killer Queens.

Rory McGrath hosts.


Ep1-Boudicca Part 1 (3rd July 2002)
The bloody story of Boudicca, Queen of the Iceni.


Ep2-Boudicca Part 2 (10th November 2002)


Ep3-Matilda (17th November 2002)
Empress Matilda, a woman who nearly became the first Queen of England


Ep4-Isabella (24th November 2002)
Queen Isabella who plotted the murder of her husband Edward II.


Ep5-Mary Tudor (1st December 2002)
Queen Mary who burned over 250 Protestants during her reign.


Ep6-Lady Mary Banks (8th December 2002)
The story of Lady Mary Bankes, a military commander during the English Civil War, who was responsible for the defence of Corfe Castle in Dorset against the parliamentary forces.
